You can use the [updateSearchIndex()](https://mongodb.github.io/node-mongodb-native/7.1/classes/Collection.html#updateSearchIndex) method to update a
MongoDB Search or MongoDB Vector Search index by providing a new index definition.

The following code shows how to use the `updateSearchIndex()` method to
update a MongoDB Search index called `search1` to change the type of the
`description` field to a string:

```javascript
// Updates a search index
const index2 = {
    "mappings": {
        "dynamic": true,
        "fields": {
            "description": {
                "type": "string"
            }
        }
    }
}
await collection.updateSearchIndex("search1", index2);
```

